    "body": "This repo might be good to help validate gas costs: https://github.com/mds1/convex-shutdown-simulation\r\n\r\nWhen simulating at bock number 14,121,827 both Hardhat and Tenderly agree the gas used is 17,143,595 (the README in that repo is currently outdated). Running the simulation in the tenderly UI (or if you wanted to parse the JSON response from their API) you'll see the total gas used before refunds is 20,872,695, and the amount of gas refunded was 3,729,100",
