    "body": "Latest numbers dropped and it seems that we are still a little bit off: https://github.com/mds1/convex-shutdown-simulation/pull/16\r\n\r\nIf we add the instrinsic to Foundry's result it gives us 22,583,004 which is 2,995 gas higher than the 22,580,009 that Tenderly, Ganache and Hardhat agree on\r\n\r\nEdit: Thinking about this more, Ganache/Tenderly/Hardhat do not have the overhead of the call to `testShutdownCost`, which may explain the discrepancy given it does a cold SLOAD + the function lookup thingamajig's cost + the cost of a `CALL` opcode?",
